race.comment: WHAT YOU WISH FOR (7) has had a couple of runs back from a spell, and was doing his best work late when finishing sixth over 1600m at Ellerslie last start. The extra 500m is ideal for him third up, and with 3.5kg less to carry, he is good enough to take this out. THE ODYSSEY (3) was well in the market and finished seventh over 2000m at Ellerslie in a race that may have come too soon for him. He loves this trip, with four wins from six starts, and can make amends here. LIVID SKY (13) stuck on well for third over a mile at Ellerslie last time out, making it back-to-back placings. She steps out to a more suitable middle distance here, and at the weights, she is worth keeping safe. SHARP 'N' SMART (1) is edging closer to a win after two consecutive placings, most recently finishing third in the G3 Balmerino Stakes over 2000m at Ellerslie 18 days ago. We all know what he is capable of when right, and he can break his win drought in this. MIDNIGHT BLUE (4) has some rough top 4 claims.
